{"000-section": {"000-title": "Indian Railways Passenger Travel Insurance Scheme Starts", "001-normal": "The scheme will be applicable for passengers holding confirmed, RAC or wait listed ticket.", "002-normal": "Under the scheme, the insurance company would pay the nominee a sum of Rs. 10 Lakh in case of death or total disability. 7.5 Lakh in case of partial disability, upto Rs 2 lakh for hospitalization expenses and Rs 10,000 for transportation of mortal remains from the place of a train accident or where an untoward incident, including terrorist attack, dacoity, rioting, shootout or arson, occurs.", "003-normal": "The premium will not be refunded in case of cancellation of the ticket."}}